DRIVERS are facing miles of queuing traffic after a lorry caught fire on the motorway.The tanker is thought to have caught alight on the hard shoulder of the M74 around 10.30am.The vehicle was travelling between the Draffan and Millbank junctions when the blaze broke out, forcing police to close the road in both directions.Diversions have been put in place and drivers are being advised to avoid the area if possible.A police spokeswoman said: &quot; We were called to a report of a lorry on fire around 10.30am on the mM74 near junction 10.&quot;There are no reports of any injuries.&quot;